--Number Guessing Game--
A simple command-line game written in Java where you try to guess a randomly chosen number between 1 and 100.

How It Works:
The computer picks a secret number between 1 and 100.
You have 10 attempts to guess it.
After each guess, you get a hint if you are close or far away from your number.


**How to Run**
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone "https://github.com/Sazxd/number-guessing-game.git"

# 2. Go into the folder
cd number-guessing-game

# 3. Compile
javac GuessGame.java

# 4. Play!
java GuessGame



Built With:
